      "comment_id" : 136951716,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@scarface This simply tells Jackson to exclude the fields <code>hibernateLazyInitializer</code> and <code>handler</code> from serialization."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7836979,
      "reputation" : 1331,
      "user_id" : 7581696,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Wy4iz.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "N. berouain",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7581696/n-berouain"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1493823390,
    "creation_date" : 1493823390,
    "answer_id" : 43763580,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had a similar problem with lazy loading via the hibernate proxy object. Got around it by annotating the class having lazy loaded private properties with:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonIgnoreProperties({\"hibernateLazyInitializer\", \"handler\"})\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7143160,
      "reputation" : 455,
      "user_id" : 5459951,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 47,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/20a046bac5aa8c1ce9f9318fd28845e0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "yellow",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5459951/yellow"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1509467007,
    "creation_date" : 1509467007,
    "answer_id" : 47040080,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Though I added getters and setters I was getting the same error. Later I found a bug, that is by Sonar's advice I cgahnged the getters and setters as protected which was causing the issue. Once I fixed that it worked as exppected.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4888255,
      "reputation" : 4910,
      "user_id" : 3940047,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bbc0ab5bfb221a19b50af3256368a038?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Pavan Kumar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3940047/pavan-kumar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1517388293,
    "creation_date" : 1517388293,
    "answer_id" : 48537909,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had the same problem for a child class where I had control, object mapper was in a common module and was inaccessible. I solved it by adding this annotation for my child class whose object was to be serialized.</p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonAutoDetect(fieldVisibility = JsonAutoDetect.Visibility.ANY)\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3092120,
      "reputation" : 1688,
      "user_id" : 2618036,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fdb602439c78c24083769286e12fbb2a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "georger",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2618036/georger"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1530875238,
    "creation_date" : 1530875238,
    "answer_id" : 51209044,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I found at least three ways of doing this:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Add <code>public getters</code> on your entity that you try to serialize;</li>\n<li>Add an annotation at the top of the entity, if you don't want <code>public getters</code>. This will change the default for Jackson from <code>Visbility=DEFAULT</code> to <code>@JsonAutoDetect(fieldVisibility = JsonAutoDetect.Visibility.ANY)</code> where any access modifiers are accepted;</li>\n<li>Change your <code>ObjectMapper</code> globally by setting <code>objectMapperInstance.setVisibility(JsonMethod.FIELD, Visibility.ANY);</code>. This should be avoided if you don't need this functionality globally.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Choose based on your needs.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8647458,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 6474268,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0b3bb92b9a985ae8025872956f003753?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Santhosh Kumar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6474268/santhosh-kumar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1533717323,
    "last_edit_date" : 1533717323,
    "creation_date" : 1533715630,
    "answer_id" : 51741603,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here are the three options:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Data/class that's been accessed needs to be <code>public</code></li>\n<li>If not <code>public</code>, add <strong>getters &amp; setters</strong></li>\n<li>Or add <code>@JsonIgnore(\"context\")</code></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
