      "comment_id" : 101823157,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This helped me! But in my opinion, you should inject the ObjectMapper of the context and configure it afterward rather than creating a new one."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 13997893,
      "reputation" : 79,
      "user_id" : 10110254,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/QyjV0.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Janus",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10110254/janus"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1536400686,
    "creation_date" : 1536400686,
    "answer_id" : 52234132,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>SpringBoot2.0 ，I resolve it by follow code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Bean public ObjectMapper objectMapper() {\n return new ObjectMapper().disable(SerializationFeature.FAIL_ON_EMPTY_BEANS);}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9975838,
      "reputation" : 51,
      "user_id" : 7380479,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8bca9ce1634134374bb02091774960a3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "raveendra_bikkina",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7380479/raveendra-bikkina"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1570255147,
    "last_edit_date" : 1570255147,
    "creation_date" : 1570254734,
    "answer_id" : 58245735,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Please use this at class level for the bean:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonIgnoreProperties(value={\"hibernateLazyInitializer\",\"handler\",\"fieldHandler\"})\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6995802,
      "reputation" : 15,
      "user_id" : 5363534,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1b002a101913341eb65aa81a3cba47a6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Satya Prakash",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5363534/satya-prakash"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1580996141,
    "last_edit_date" : 1580996141,
    "creation_date" : 1580989831,
    "answer_id" : 60094326,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>adding setter and getter will also solve the issue as it fixed for me.\n For Ex:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class TestA {\n    String SomeString = \"asd\";\n\n    public String getSomeString () {        return SomeString ;     }\n\n    public void setSomeString (String SS ) {        SomeString = SS ;   } \n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 18005107,
      "reputation" : 31,
      "user_id" : 13086073,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/80478c39a0711af0348d4025d9ae7d3e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
