    "last_activity_date" : 1608646331,
    "creation_date" : 1608646331,
    "answer_id" : 65410192,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you use Lomdok libraray (<a href=\"https://projectlombok.org/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://projectlombok.org/</a>) then add <code>@Data</code> (<a href=\"https://projectlombok.org/features/Data\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://projectlombok.org/features/Data</a>) annotation to your data object class.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4776516,
      "reputation" : 586,
      "user_id" : 3859455,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ff45c522cd1db2b19725eddca2715e00?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Nakesh",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3859455/nakesh"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1634030796,
    "creation_date" : 1634030796,
    "answer_id" : 69538081,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Jackson uses getters and setters serialization./deserialization.\nSo add getter and setter in your model class.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 15032849,
      "reputation" : 602,
      "user_id" : 10850340,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cb7a66fd436aded59244e6fb002feb1a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "j.xavier.atero",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10850340/j-xavier-atero"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1661503012,
    "last_edit_date" : 1661503012,
    "creation_date" : 1661502201,
    "answer_id" : 73498076,
    "question_id" : 8367312,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For me, the problem was the annotation <code>@RestResource(exported = false)</code> from the <code>import org.springframework.data.rest.core.annotation.RestResource</code>. Which I forgot to remove.</p>\n<p>Also, I got the same error when I forgot to add the class annotation <code>@XmlRootElement</code> from the <code>import javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 12114036,
      "reputation" : 589,
      "user_id" : 9950567,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-c4t2Z1m53Vc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAECM/Ptgw8WrAw_U/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Sham Fiorin",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9950567/sham-fiorin"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
